  "body": "### Description\r\nCurrently, Teku's default storage mode is `PRUNE` which downloads all historic blocks but prunes finalized states. Ultimately we want the default to become `MINIMAL` without unnecessarily surprising users.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n* for any existing database, the default storage mode should be `PRUNE`.\r\n* for new databases the default storage mode should be `MINIMAL`\r\n* for any database the user can override the default by explicitly setting `--data-storage-mode`\r\n* once the user has switched an existing database to `MINIMAL` mode, the default storage mode should be `MINIMAL`\r\n\r\nOne option worth considering is to make the default storage mode always whatever storage mode was last used for that database.\r\n\r\nAlso, we should add a log with the database mode being used (if Teku does not do this).\r\n\r\nThis follows on from #6576",
